.nh
.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-bench - Benchmark an OpenAI-compatible inference endpoint


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel bench  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Run performance benchmarks against OpenAI-compatible inference endpoints.

.PP
Measures tokens/sec, latency, and time-to-first-token (TTFT) using streaming
chat completions. Supports multi-turn conversations and concurrent requests.

.PP
The endpoint should serve the OpenAI-compatible /v1/chat/completions API
(vLLM, SGLang, Ollama, etc). The URL can be a base URL or the full path.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--compare\fP=""
	Second endpoint URL for side-by-side comparison

.PP
\fB--concurrency\fP="1"
	Number of parallel requests

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for bench

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	Output results as JSON

.PP
\fB--max-tokens\fP=50
	Maximum tokens to generate per turn

.PP
\fB--model\fP=""
	Model name (auto-detected from /v1/models if not set)

.PP
\fB--turns\fP=1
	Number of conversation turns


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  citadel bench http://localhost:8000
  citadel bench http://gpu-node:30000 --model qwen2-72b --max-tokens 200
  citadel bench http://localhost:8000 --turns 3 --concurrency 4
  citadel bench http://localhost:8000 --compare http://localhost:30000
  citadel bench http://localhost:8000 --json
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP
